<ContentLayout title="Getting Here" description="Getting to the Ith-Region by car, train and bus." heroImage="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1449824913935-59a10b8d2000?w=1920&h=800&fit=crop" heroImageAlt="Road through countryside" heroSubtitle="How to reach the Ith-Region">
  <h2>By Car</h2>
  <p>The Ith-Region is conveniently located in the Weserbergland, accessible via the <strong>A7</strong> motorway and <strong>B1</strong> road.</p>
  <ul>
    <li>From <strong>Hannover</strong>: approx. 50 km (45 min)</li>
    <li>From <strong>Hildesheim</strong>: approx. 30 km (30 min)</li>
    <li>From <strong>Hameln</strong>: approx. 25 km (25 min)</li>
    <li>From <strong>Göttingen</strong>: approx. 80 km (60 min)</li>
  </ul>
  <h2>By Public Transport</h2>
  <p>Salzhemmendorf is reachable by bus from Hameln. Please note that services are limited on weekends and during school holidays.</p>
  <h2>Trailhead Parking</h2>
  <p>Several free car parks are available as starting points for Ith hikes. See our <a href="/en/discover/map/">interactive map</a>.</p>
</ContentLayout>
